description: An illustration of a jukebox, most likely modeled after the iconic 1946 Wurlitzer Model 1015. There are bright pastel shapes in light blue, purple, pink, and yellow around the top edge of the jukebox and around the center representing neon lights. In the center of the jukebox are downward-facing triangles of alternating brown and darker brown shades representing the door casting. The CD catalog and record player are representing by dark gray shapes against light blue backgrounds.
